text: Web Developer | Full-Stack Engineer | Software Engineer
description: This section shows the candidate is targeting roles that are relevant to the job description, which seeks software engineers. It directly showcases their interest and expertise in the software engineering domain.

text: Languages: Javascript, Python, Typescript, HTML, CSS, SQL
description: The candidate highlights proficiency in several languages mentioned in the Amazon job description (Python). HTML, CSS, and Javascript are useful for prime video given the vast number of devices it runs on.

text: Cloud Platforms (AWS, GCP, Azure), Docker, Regex, Heroku, Git, Kubernetes, Terraform, Agile Project Management, CI/CD
description: This demonstrates experience with cloud platforms (especially AWS, which is specifically mentioned as a plus in the Amazon job description). Knowledge of Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform, and CI/CD indicates DevOps skills, desirable for building and deploying microservices.

This is a direct and relevant experience match. The description for Arize AI focuses on cloud infrastructure and maintenance, which aligns with Amazon's requirement for building highly scalable distributed services.

text: Successfully upgraded Arize within customer infrastructure, maintaining the health and performance of clusters.
description: This is a relevant experience match, showing experience with maintaining infrastructure. Successfully Upgrading within customer infrastructure suggests practical experience in a real world environment.

The 'Sales Support Representative' role is less relevant. While it highlights skills such as communication and problem-solving, it is not directly related to software engineering. This section could be improved by focusing on transferable skills or omitting it if space is needed for more relevant experiences.

text: Certification: Full Stack Software Engineer: JavaScript, Python, HTML, CSS, React, Redux, Node.js, Express, SQL
description: While mentioning technologies, it doesn't provide enough context. Providing a brief description of the App Academy curriculum or key projects completed during the certification would be more valuable. Also, while the certification includes mention of relevant technologies, it is still just a certification. Having a project to work on would show more tangible benefits.

The 'Bachelor of Science in Computer Science' should be moved to the top. Also, the object oriented programming course listed should be expanded to make it more clear what knowledge the person has and show that it lines up with the Java or C++ mentioned in the basic requirements.

The 'Freelance' experience lacks specific details about the scale and complexity of the projects. Quantifying the impact or providing more technical details about the challenges overcome and solutions implemented would make this section stronger. Vague descriptions like 'Crafted unique websites' and 'Developed strong rapport' do not showcase technical skills as much.

text: Experience implementing and consuming large scale web services.
description: The CV should more explicitly mention experience with web services. This could be incorporated by describing how the current cloud experience relates to web service architecture, or elaborating on the 'large scale web services' experience in a way that is more quantitative.
